                            <comment id="43742" author="luke" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2009 13:06:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is more an issue with the standard maven skin and the Spring version on sourceforge which the current site is based on. There is no maven-base.css in the project, though we can of course set up the same defaults in site.css.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve edited the files for the existing deployed sites in-situ, but the chances are we won&apos;t be using the maven-spring-skin for the next release unless someone gets a chance to update the look and feel to match the current incarnation of springsource.org. I&apos;ll probably be falling back to a default site css file for the next release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43748" author="luke" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2009 18:20:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve modified site.css, which should hopefuly do the trick in future deployments, until the maven skin is updated and we decide to use it again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
